Autoplot

Source: R/plot.R
autoplot.fitdist.Rd

Autoplot

# S3 method for fitdist
autoplot(object, ci = FALSE, hc = 5L,
  xlab = "Concentration", ylab = "Species Affected", ...)

Arguments

object

The object to plot.
ci

A flag indicating wether to plot confidence intervals
hc

A count between 1 and 99 indicating the percent hazard concentration to plot (or NULL).
xlab

A string of the x-axis label.
ylab

A string of the x-axis label.
...

Unused.

Examples

autoplot(boron_lnorm)
#> Warning: Removed 98 rows containing missing values (geom_path).
#> geom_path: Each group consists of only one observation. Do you need to adjust
#> the group aesthetic?
